<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I don't need her.
I need Louis,</b></i></font>

159
00:06:17,128 --> 00:06:18,087
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and I don't know
where he is.</b></i></font>

160
00:06:18,171 --> 00:06:19,172
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Well, why didn't you
start with that?</b></i></font>

161
00:06:19,255 --> 00:06:20,590
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>He had an emergency
meeting with a client</b></i></font>

162
00:06:20,673 --> 00:06:21,966
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and he ran out of here.
When?</b></i></font>

163
00:06:22,050 --> 00:06:23,301
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Half an hour ago.</b></i></font>

164
00:06:23,676 --> 00:06:25,261
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I saw him at the elevators
before he left.</b></i></font>

165
00:06:25,344 --> 00:06:27,221
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You tell him
the second he gets back,</b></i></font>

166
00:06:27,305 --> 00:06:28,431
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I need to talk to him.</b></i></font>

167
00:06:28,806 --> 00:06:29,974
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Harvey,
what's going on?</b></i></font>

168
00:06:31,684 --> 00:06:33,728
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Jim Reynolds is
threatening to leave.
What?</b></i></font>

169
00:06:34,395 --> 00:06:36,481
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Harvey, I was there
the night he put
Jessica on notice.</b></i></font>

170
00:06:36,564 --> 00:06:37,690
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>If he's leaving,
then you don't have time</b></i></font>

171
00:06:37,815 --> 00:06:39,025
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>to wait for Louis.
I know.</b></i></font>

172
00:06:39,150 --> 00:06:40,568
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But if I can't make it
work with Reynolds,</b></i></font>

173
00:06:40,651 --> 00:06:42,236
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm going to need Louis
the second I get back.</b></i></font>

174
00:06:42,612 --> 00:06:43,654
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm on it.</b></i></font>

175
00:06:48,409 --> 00:06:49,577
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>CASEY: What the hell
is this?</b></i></font>

176
00:06:49,660 --> 00:06:50,870
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You know what that is.
It's a subpoena.</b></i></font>

177
00:06:51,287 --> 00:06:53,873
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I signed your affidavit.
You have what you need.</b></i></font>

178
00:06:53,956 --> 00:06:56,834
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Did you really think
you wouldn't have to testify
that Bailey had an alibi?</b></i></font>

179
00:06:56,918 --> 00:06:57,960
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What I didn't think
was that</b></i></font>

180
00:06:58,044 --> 00:06:59,879
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>you were going to paint
me as incompetent!</b></i></font>

181
00:06:59,962 --> 00:07:02,173
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>RACHEL: We did
what you should have
done 12 years ago.</b></i></font>

182
00:07:02,256 --> 00:07:04,175
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Represent your client.</b></i></font>

183
00:07:04,383 --> 00:07:06,636
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And you weren't
even forming sentences
when I handled this case.</b></i></font>

184
00:07:06,719 --> 00:07:08,262
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>RACHEL:
Well, I'm forming
sentences now.</b></i></font>

185
00:07:08,346 --> 00:07:09,430
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>So, instead of being angry,</b></i></font>

186
00:07:09,514 --> 00:07:11,390
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>you should be thanking us
for not bringing an action</b></i></font>

187
00:07:11,474 --> 00:07:13,142
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>against you
on Leonard's behalf.</b></i></font>

188
00:07:13,226 --> 00:07:14,769
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Bring it on.</b></i></font>

189
00:07:14,852 --> 00:07:16,104
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Georgina,
you made a mistake.</b></i></font>

190
00:07:16,187 --> 00:07:17,730
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>We're giving you
the chance to fix it</b></i></font>

191
00:07:17,814 --> 00:07:19,107
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>whether you like it
or not.</b></i></font>

192
00:07:19,190 --> 00:07:21,442
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I don't give a shit
what you think
you're doing.</b></i></font>

193
00:07:21,526 --> 00:07:22,944
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm not here
to fix it.</b></i></font>

194
00:07:23,027 --> 00:07:24,237
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm here
because of this.</b></i></font>

195
00:07:24,862 --> 00:07:26,197
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then I'll see you
on the stand.</b></i></font>

196
00:07:31,244 --> 00:07:32,453
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>REYNOLDS: Harvey,
what are you doing here?</b></i></font>

197
00:07:32,537 --> 00:07:34,372
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm here to stop you
from breaking your word.</b></i></font>

198
00:07:34,539 --> 00:07:35,790
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then I suggest
you turn around</b></i></font>

199
00:07:35,873 --> 00:07:37,250
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and walk out of here
as fast as you can.</b></i></font>

200
00:07:37,375 --> 00:07:38,459
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Look, just hear me out.</b></i></font>

201
00:07:38,543 --> 00:07:39,919
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>The night
you spoke to Jessica,</b></i></font>

202
00:07:40,169 --> 00:07:43,256
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>we'd lost 75%
of our revenue stream.
But since then...</b></i></font>

203
00:07:43,339 --> 00:07:44,465
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Listen to me.</b></i></font>

204
00:07:44,549 --> 00:07:47,301
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>My taking meetings
has nothing to do
with your revenue stream.</b></i></font>

205
00:07:47,385 --> 00:07:48,511
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then what the hell
is this about?</b></i></font>

206
00:07:48,594 --> 00:07:50,596
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>MAN: It's about
the rumors that you tanked
William Sutter's case.</b></i></font>

207
00:07:51,180 --> 00:07:52,849
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I didn't tank shit.</b></i></font>

208
00:07:52,932 --> 00:07:54,809
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I told them that.
I don't believe any of it.</b></i></font>

209
00:07:54,892 --> 00:07:56,561
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Well, it doesn't matter
what you believe, Jim,</b></i></font>

210
00:07:56,686 --> 00:07:57,812
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>because the board
believes it.</b></i></font>

211
00:07:57,895 --> 00:07:59,480
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And let me guess,
you're the board.</b></i></font>

212
00:07:59,564 --> 00:08:01,983
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Donald Mannis.
I'd shake your hand,</b></i></font>

213
00:08:02,066 --> 00:08:04,527
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>but I wouldn't want
your shady ethics
rubbing off on me.</b></i></font>

214
00:08:04,610 --> 00:08:06,863
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>The only thing that's
rubbing off on you, Donald,</b></i></font>

215
00:08:06,946 --> 00:08:09,365
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>is the load of bullshit
from William Sutter.</b></i></font>

216
00:08:09,824 --> 00:08:12,034
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Your former associate
was in prison
with his son-in-law</b></i></font>

217
00:08:12,118 --> 00:08:14,412
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and the day
Sutter goes down,
your guy gets out.</b></i></font>

218
00:08:14,495 --> 00:08:17,123
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You may call that bullshit,
but his story adds up to me.</b></i></font>

219
00:08:17,623 --> 00:08:19,208
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And this company
can't have an attorney</b></i></font>

220
00:08:19,292 --> 00:08:21,836
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>who's willing to turn
on his own client.</b></i></font>

221
00:08:24,881 --> 00:08:26,340
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You see
what I'm dealing with?</b></i></font>

222
00:08:26,424 --> 00:08:29,510
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I only took those meetings
because I'm being pressured
to take those meetings.</b></i></font>

223
00:08:29,594 --> 00:08:31,804
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I get it. That asshole
wants your job.</b></i></font>

224
00:08:31,888 --> 00:08:33,014
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>He doesn't
just want it.</b></i></font>

225
00:08:33,097 --> 00:08:34,849
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>If I don't let you go,
he's going to get it.</b></i></font>

226
00:08:34,932 --> 00:08:36,517
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And the one thing
that might have
changed that</b></i></font>

227
00:08:36,601 --> 00:08:38,102
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>was Jessica coming in here
and showing him</b></i></font>

228
00:08:38,186 --> 00:08:39,395
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>how important
we are to her.</b></i></font>

229
00:08:39,812 --> 00:08:41,647
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You are important
to her, Jim.</b></i></font>

230
00:08:41,731 --> 00:08:43,232
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But Jessica's in trial
right now.</b></i></font>

231
00:08:43,316 --> 00:08:44,567
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then you should have
sent Louis Litt.</b></i></font>

232
00:08:44,650 --> 00:08:46,235
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Because the last thing
that asshole needed to see</b></i></font>

233
00:08:46,319 --> 00:08:48,237
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>when he walked
in here was you!</b></i></font>

234
00:08:56,746 --> 00:08:58,706
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Your Honor,
permission to treat
the witness as hostile.</b></i></font>

235
00:08:58,789 --> 00:08:59,874
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>On what grounds?</b></i></font>

236
00:08:59,957 --> 00:09:01,918
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>The witness hasn't
even said anything yet.</b></i></font>

237
00:09:02,001 --> 00:09:03,502
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>On the grounds
that five minutes ago,</b></i></font>

238
00:09:03,586 --> 00:09:04,921
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>she told me she'd sooner</b></i></font>

239
00:09:05,004 --> 00:09:06,714
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>deny Leonard Bailey
a new trial</b></i></font>

240
00:09:06,797 --> 00:09:08,633
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>than to risk
looking incompetent.</b></i></font>

241
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:11,219
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>JUDGE EVANS:
Is this true?</b></i></font>

242
00:09:11,302 --> 00:09:12,345
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Yes.</b></i></font>

243
00:09:12,553 --> 00:09:13,971
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then permission granted.</b></i></font>

244
00:09:14,805 --> 00:09:17,225
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Miss Casey, when you
were Leonard Bailey's
public defender,</b></i></font>

245
00:09:17,308 --> 00:09:19,852
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>did he tell you that,
at the time of the murders,</b></i></font>

246
00:09:19,936 --> 00:09:22,355
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>he was in the apartment
of a woman named
Maria Gomez?</b></i></font>

247
00:09:22,605 --> 00:09:23,648
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Yes.</b></i></font>

248
00:09:23,731 --> 00:09:25,733
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>JESSICA: Which means
he not only had an alibi,</b></i></font>

249
00:09:25,816 --> 00:09:28,402
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>he had a witness
that could testify to it.
Is that correct?</b></i></font>

250
00:09:28,486 --> 00:09:29,528
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Yes.</b></i></font>

251
00:09:29,612 --> 00:09:32,990
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then why in God's name
didn't that witness
ever take the stand?</b></i></font>

252
00:09:33,157 --> 00:09:35,368
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Because she left town
without telling anyone</b></i></font>

253
00:09:35,451 --> 00:09:36,953
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>right before
the trial started.</b></i></font>

254
00:09:37,078 --> 00:09:38,955
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Did you try
to locate her?
Yes, I did.</b></i></font>

255
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:40,748
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>How hard
did you look?
I did my best.</b></i></font>

256
00:09:40,831 --> 00:09:42,667
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>The truth is,
you didn't look for her
at all, did you?</b></i></font>

257
00:09:42,750 --> 00:09:43,793
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>CASEY:
That's not true.</b></i></font>

258
00:09:43,876 --> 00:09:45,419
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I did everything I could
to try to find her.</b></i></font>

259
00:09:45,503 --> 00:09:46,504
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>JESSICA:
But you didn't.</b></i></font>

260
00:09:46,587 --> 00:09:49,090
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And if you had,
there would have been
an alibi witness</b></i></font>

261
00:09:49,173 --> 00:09:50,174
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>that would have
told the jury</b></i></font>

262
00:09:50,258 --> 00:09:51,842
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>that he couldn't possibly
have committed those murders.</b></i></font>

263
00:09:51,926 --> 00:09:54,262
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>That witness
was a drug addict
with a prior conviction.</b></i></font>

264
00:09:54,345 --> 00:09:55,930
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And she would have been
eviscerated on the stand.</b></i></font>

265
00:09:56,013 --> 00:09:58,808
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then why did you
try to find her at all?</b></i></font>

266
00:10:01,394 --> 00:10:03,020
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Let me suggest an answer.</b></i></font>

267
00:10:03,562 --> 00:10:06,274
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You did try to find her
because you knew
if you did,</b></i></font>

268
00:10:06,357 --> 00:10:08,025
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Leonard Bailey
would be found innocent.</b></i></font>

269
00:10:08,192 --> 00:10:09,610
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But you dropped the ball.</b></i></font>

270
00:10:09,694 --> 00:10:12,530
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Leonard Bailey
went to death row.</b></i></font>

271
00:10:14,073 --> 00:10:17,702
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And you'd rather
let him stay there
than to admit the truth.</b></i></font>

272
00:10:23,082 --> 00:10:24,834
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Ms. Casey,
in your estimation,</b></i></font>

273
00:10:24,917 --> 00:10:26,460
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>was Leonard Bailey innocent?</b></i></font>

274
00:10:26,544 --> 00:10:27,712
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>JESSICA:
Objection, Your Honor.</b></i></font>

275
00:10:27,795 --> 00:10:28,838
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Calls for
a conclusion.</b></i></font>

276
00:10:28,921 --> 00:10:30,756
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Your Honor, they opened
the door to this</b></i></font>

277
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,300
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>when they put her
on the stand.</b></i></font>

278
00:10:32,383 --> 00:10:34,885
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And no one is
more qualified to answer</b></i></font>

279
00:10:35,094 --> 00:10:37,638
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>than his own attorney.
JUDGE EVANS:
I'll allow it.</b></i></font>

280
00:10:37,972 --> 00:10:39,056
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Miss Casey?</b></i></font>

281
00:10:39,557 --> 00:10:41,600
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I thought
Leonard Bailey was guilty.</b></i></font>

282
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:44,228
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And I still do.</b></i></font>

283
00:10:48,190 --> 00:10:50,318
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Louis, the next time
you have an emergency meeting,</b></i></font>

284
00:10:50,401 --> 00:10:51,527
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>you better
clear it with me.</b></i></font>

285
00:10:51,610 --> 00:10:53,487
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'll keep that in mind
for the future, Harvey.</b></i></font>

286
00:10:53,571 --> 00:10:55,656
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But the reason I had
an emergency meeting
was you.</b></i></font>

287
00:10:55,740 --> 00:10:56,824
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What the hell
are you talking about?</b></i></font>

288
00:10:56,907 --> 00:10:58,200
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Jensen Analytics
heard a rumor</b></i></font>

289
00:10:58,284 --> 00:10:59,452
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>that you tanked
Sutter's case</b></i></font>

290
00:10:59,535 --> 00:11:00,536
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and they're threatening
to walk.</b></i></font>

291
00:11:00,953 --> 00:11:01,954
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Shit.
What did you tell them?</b></i></font>

292
00:11:02,038 --> 00:11:02,997
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What do you think
I told them?</b></i></font>

293
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,540
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I told him William Sutter's
a lying son of a bitch</b></i></font>

294
00:11:04,623 --> 00:11:06,125
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>who will do or say anything
to get what he wants.</b></i></font>

295
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:08,336
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What did they say?
They said if Jessica's
oldest client is leaving,</b></i></font>

296
00:11:08,419 --> 00:11:09,503
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>why should they stay?</b></i></font>

297
00:11:09,587 --> 00:11:10,963
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>God damn it!</b></i></font>

298
00:11:11,088 --> 00:11:12,548
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>LOUIS: Harvey,
if they think that,</b></i></font>

299
00:11:12,631 --> 00:11:13,966
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>then it's just
a matter of time</b></i></font>

300
00:11:14,050 --> 00:11:15,676
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>until all of our clients
think that.</b></i></font>

301
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:17,970
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Which means we need
to get Jim Reynolds to stay.</b></i></font>

302
00:11:18,054 --> 00:11:19,305
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What are we
gonna tell Jessica?</b></i></font>

303
00:11:19,388 --> 00:11:21,849
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>We're gonna tell her
if she doesn't do something
about Reynolds soon,</b></i></font>

304
00:11:21,932 --> 00:11:24,185
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>she's not going to have
a firm to come back to.</b></i></font>

305
00:11:37,448 --> 00:11:38,908
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>MIKE: Hey.</b></i></font>

306
00:11:38,991 --> 00:11:40,034
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Hey.</b></i></font>

307
00:11:41,285 --> 00:11:43,662
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Rachel, listen to me.
It went as well
as it could have.</b></i></font>

308
00:11:43,746 --> 00:11:45,206
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You don't have to
look so worried.</b></i></font>

309
00:11:45,289 --> 00:11:47,208
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>How can I
not look worried?</b></i></font>

310
00:11:47,666 --> 00:11:50,503
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Mike, that woman said
that she thought
he was guilty</b></i></font>

311
00:11:50,586 --> 00:11:52,171
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and the prosecutor
got it on record.</b></i></font>

312
00:11:52,254 --> 00:11:53,798
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And Jessica
got it on record</b></i></font>

313
00:11:53,881 --> 00:11:55,674
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>that she was incompetent
before he did that.</b></i></font>

314
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:58,386
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And the jury heard it.
Yeah, but you saw
the jury as well as I did.</b></i></font>

315
00:11:58,469 --> 00:11:59,595
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>They're not convinced.</b></i></font>

316
00:12:01,597 --> 00:12:02,640
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Put Leonard on the stand.</b></i></font>

317
