<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Leonard, is there
something that you would
like to say to her?</b></i></font>

478
00:18:31,028 --> 00:18:34,948
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I lost 12 years
for a crime
I didn't commit.</b></i></font>

479
00:18:37,034 --> 00:18:38,702
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But I won't regret
any of it</b></i></font>

480
00:18:39,495 --> 00:18:42,664
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>if it ends up
being the thing
that got me clean</b></i></font>

481
00:18:43,040 --> 00:18:44,541
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and reunited with you.</b></i></font>

482
00:18:46,668 --> 00:18:49,171
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(VOICE BREAKS)
Because if I died,</b></i></font>

483
00:18:49,254 --> 00:18:51,215
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>with you believing
your father did this...</b></i></font>

484
00:18:51,298 --> 00:18:52,549
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>RACHEL: (SOFTLY)
She doesn't think that.</b></i></font>

485
00:18:52,883 --> 00:18:56,053
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>She knows that
you didn't hurt those kids.</b></i></font>

486
00:19:00,265 --> 00:19:01,725
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I have no further questions,
Your Honor.</b></i></font>

487
00:19:04,019 --> 00:19:06,897
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Your Honor, we reserve
the right to cross-examine
the defendant.</b></i></font>

488
00:19:07,022 --> 00:19:08,065
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But for now,</b></i></font>

489
00:19:08,232 --> 00:19:10,317
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>since he's claiming
he knows what it feels like</b></i></font>

490
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,985
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>to be an aggrieved father,</b></i></font>

491
00:19:12,069 --> 00:19:14,112
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'd like to call
Victor Forrest to the stand.</b></i></font>

492
00:19:21,662 --> 00:19:23,831
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Thank you for agreeing
to do this, Mr. Forrest.</b></i></font>

493
00:19:25,082 --> 00:19:26,583
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I know how difficult
it must be for you.</b></i></font>

494
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:28,043
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Would you mind
telling us</b></i></font>

495
00:19:28,126 --> 00:19:29,419
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>a little bit
about your daughter?</b></i></font>

496
00:19:29,628 --> 00:19:30,879
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>VICTOR:
What can I say?</b></i></font>

497
00:19:31,129 --> 00:19:32,130
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Kim was
our everything.</b></i></font>

498
00:19:32,214 --> 00:19:33,966
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>She was sweet, kind.</b></i></font>

499
00:19:35,050 --> 00:19:36,426
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Incredible sense of humor.</b></i></font>

500
00:19:36,885 --> 00:19:38,136
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>LARRY: She played soccer,
didn't she?</b></i></font>

501
00:19:38,595 --> 00:19:40,430
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I used to watch her run
up and down the field.</b></i></font>

502
00:19:42,182 --> 00:19:43,183
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Never got tired.</b></i></font>

503
00:19:43,267 --> 00:19:45,352
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>She just kept running
with a big smile on her face.</b></i></font>

504
00:19:46,436 --> 00:19:48,021
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(VOICE BREAKS)
She had such
a beautiful smile.</b></i></font>

505
00:19:48,772 --> 00:19:50,357
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>LARRY: It's obvious
you loved her very much.</b></i></font>

506
00:19:50,607 --> 00:19:51,608
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>VICTOR:
I didn't just love her.</b></i></font>

507
00:19:51,692 --> 00:19:52,818
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I tried to protect her.</b></i></font>

508
00:19:53,277 --> 00:19:55,571
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I warned her
about boys, drugs.</b></i></font>

509
00:19:56,947 --> 00:19:59,074
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And I said,
"If you're ever in trouble,
you call me."</b></i></font>

510
00:19:59,157 --> 00:20:00,242
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And the thing
that gets me is,</b></i></font>

511
00:20:01,618 --> 00:20:04,121
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>she did call that night.
Not to say
she was in trouble.</b></i></font>

512
00:20:05,622 --> 00:20:06,999
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>To say she was
coming home.</b></i></font>

513
00:20:07,457 --> 00:20:08,667
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But she never did
make it home.</b></i></font>

514
00:20:08,750 --> 00:20:09,793
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>VICTOR: No.</b></i></font>

515
00:20:09,877 --> 00:20:12,421
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And I don't care
what some junkie witness
was going to say.</b></i></font>

516
00:20:13,463 --> 00:20:16,508
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>They found
that animal standing over
my little girl's body,</b></i></font>

517
00:20:16,717 --> 00:20:18,218
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>her blood all over him.</b></i></font>

518
00:20:18,468 --> 00:20:20,804
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>He took away
my everything
in one night.</b></i></font>

519
00:20:21,597 --> 00:20:23,515
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And he did it for money
to buy more drugs.</b></i></font>

520
00:20:23,932 --> 00:20:26,602
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>LARRY: And how do you
feel about the speech
he gave to the jury?</b></i></font>

521
00:20:26,685 --> 00:20:29,354
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>He talked about
getting a second chance
with his family.</b></i></font>

522
00:20:29,771 --> 00:20:30,981
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What about my family?</b></i></font>

523
00:20:31,899 --> 00:20:33,525
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Our lives were ruined
that night.</b></i></font>

524
00:20:33,942 --> 00:20:36,153
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>My little girl never even
got a first chance.</b></i></font>

525
00:20:37,195 --> 00:20:38,822
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>No further questions,
Your Honor.</b></i></font>

526
00:20:43,493 --> 00:20:44,494
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Mr. Forrest.</b></i></font>

527
00:20:46,413 --> 00:20:49,207
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Did you actually see
Leonard Bailey
kill your daughter?</b></i></font>

528
00:20:49,625 --> 00:20:51,043
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Of course I didn't,
but that doesn't mean...</b></i></font>

529
00:20:51,126 --> 00:20:52,336
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>No further questions,
Your Honor.</b></i></font>

530
00:21:02,846 --> 00:21:04,848
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Donna, can I talk to you
for a second?</b></i></font>

531
00:21:05,349 --> 00:21:07,434
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Well, since you asked
so nicely,
I'll even give you two.</b></i></font>

532
00:21:07,726 --> 00:21:09,102
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I have some bad news
I have to give Louis.</b></i></font>

533
00:21:09,186 --> 00:21:11,063
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And since he and I
are finally in a good place...</b></i></font>

534
00:21:11,146 --> 00:21:12,314
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You want to know
how to break it to him</b></i></font>

535
00:21:12,397 --> 00:21:13,690
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>without blowing
things up again.</b></i></font>

536
00:21:13,815 --> 00:21:14,900
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Yeah.</b></i></font>

537
00:21:15,525 --> 00:21:17,152
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>How bad is it?</b></i></font>

538
00:21:17,235 --> 00:21:18,487
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>It's not good.</b></i></font>

539
00:21:19,613 --> 00:21:20,989
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then do what
you just did with me.</b></i></font>

540
00:21:21,531 --> 00:21:23,659
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Approach him with respect,
pull the Band-Aid off,</b></i></font>

541
00:21:23,742 --> 00:21:26,536
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and if you have that
same look on your face
as you do right now,</b></i></font>

542
00:21:26,912 --> 00:21:28,830
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>he'll send you
on your way
with a handshake.</b></i></font>

543
00:21:29,957 --> 00:21:31,166
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Thanks, Donna.</b></i></font>

544
00:21:32,042 --> 00:21:33,085
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Stu?</b></i></font>

545
00:21:34,711 --> 00:21:35,879
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>It was nice
having you here.</b></i></font>

546
00:21:45,889 --> 00:21:46,974
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What?</b></i></font>

547
00:21:47,224 --> 00:21:49,977
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You should have seen
yourself thunder away
at Kendrick today.</b></i></font>

548
00:21:50,060 --> 00:21:51,895
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You were amazing.
(EXHALES)</b></i></font>

549
00:21:52,396 --> 00:21:54,106
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And if I were Dawson
or Downey</b></i></font>

550
00:21:54,189 --> 00:21:57,651
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and I had to choose between
you and your father to
represent me on this?</b></i></font>

551
00:21:58,902 --> 00:22:00,487
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'd choose you
any day of the week</b></i></font>

552
00:22:00,570 --> 00:22:01,863
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and twice on Sunday.</b></i></font>

553
00:22:02,447 --> 00:22:03,448
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What are you
talking about?</b></i></font>

554
00:22:03,532 --> 00:22:04,658
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm talking about
A Few Good Men.</b></i></font>

555
00:22:04,741 --> 00:22:07,077
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Mike, I don't have time
for movie quotes right now.</b></i></font>

556
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:08,912
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm not trying to quote
a movie, Rachel.</b></i></font>

557
00:22:08,996 --> 00:22:11,748
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm trying to tell you
that it doesn't matter
what that girl's father said.</b></i></font>

558
00:22:11,832 --> 00:22:13,000
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You're still in this</b></i></font>

559
00:22:13,083 --> 00:22:14,584
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and you were great
up there.</b></i></font>

560
00:22:17,129 --> 00:22:18,630
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Wait a minute.
The father.</b></i></font>

561
00:22:20,716 --> 00:22:21,925
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>MIKE:
What about him?</b></i></font>

562
00:22:28,181 --> 00:22:30,183
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>He called Maria
a junkie witness.</b></i></font>

563
00:22:30,267 --> 00:22:31,643
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>How would he even know
that she was a drug user?</b></i></font>

564
00:22:31,727 --> 00:22:32,978
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What do you mean?
The same way I would know.</b></i></font>

565
00:22:33,061 --> 00:22:35,188
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Leonard and his public
defender said so
on the stand.</b></i></font>

566
00:22:35,814 --> 00:22:37,274
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>No, but he used
those exact words</b></i></font>

567
00:22:37,357 --> 00:22:39,401
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>when he came at me
trying to get me
to drop this whole thing.</b></i></font>

568
00:22:39,526 --> 00:22:41,361
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>He came at you?
It's fine.
I handled it.</b></i></font>

569
00:22:41,528 --> 00:22:42,988
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But he did try
to intimidate me.</b></i></font>

570
00:22:44,364 --> 00:22:45,824
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And a man who would
intimidate you</b></i></font>

571
00:22:45,907 --> 00:22:47,617
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>might do the same thing
to Maria Gomez.</b></i></font>

572
00:22:47,701 --> 00:22:49,327
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Yeah, but I don't think
he intimidated her.</b></i></font>

573
00:22:49,411 --> 00:22:51,038
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I think he did
the opposite.</b></i></font>

574
00:22:51,121 --> 00:22:52,497
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What are you saying?
I'm saying I think</b></i></font>

575
00:22:52,581 --> 00:22:54,291
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>we need to pay
that man a visit.</b></i></font>

576
00:22:58,712 --> 00:22:59,755
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Louis, do you
have a minute?</b></i></font>

577
00:22:59,838 --> 00:23:01,882
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>To tell you the truth,
Stu, I kind of have
a full plate right now.</b></i></font>

578
00:23:01,965 --> 00:23:04,384
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>So, unless it's a matter
of life and death,
I'd rather it wait.</b></i></font>

579
00:23:04,468 --> 00:23:05,469
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>This can't wait.</b></i></font>

580
00:23:07,345 --> 00:23:08,430
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>We have to move out.</b></i></font>

581
00:23:09,139 --> 00:23:10,766
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What do you mean
"move out"?
We're relocating.</b></i></font>

582
00:23:11,391 --> 00:23:14,728
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I wanted to tell you
in person so there's
no hard feelings.</b></i></font>

583
00:23:14,811 --> 00:23:16,063
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Oh, bullshit!
You can't do this.</b></i></font>

584
00:23:16,146 --> 00:23:17,147
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Louis, I don't
have a choice.</b></i></font>

585
00:23:17,272 --> 00:23:18,732
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Sutter went bankrupt
two days ago</b></i></font>

586
00:23:18,815 --> 00:23:20,484
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and they owed us
under their contract.</b></i></font>

587
00:23:20,567 --> 00:23:22,486
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>They're offering us
their space to cover
their obligations</b></i></font>

588
00:23:22,569 --> 00:23:24,488
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and I have to say yes
by tomorrow.</b></i></font>

589
00:23:24,696 --> 00:23:26,615
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You wouldn't even have
those obligations, Stu,</b></i></font>

590
00:23:26,698 --> 00:23:28,366
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>if it weren't for us.
I know that.</b></i></font>

591
00:23:28,450 --> 00:23:30,744
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But I can't tell my bosses
I'm passing on a fortune
in free rent</b></i></font>

592
00:23:30,827 --> 00:23:31,953
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>because you guys
did me a solid.</b></i></font>

593
00:23:32,037 --> 00:23:33,246
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Well, then, you tell them
you have a lease</b></i></font>

594
00:23:33,330 --> 00:23:34,539
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and I'm going to sue
your goddamn ass!</b></i></font>

595
00:23:35,457 --> 00:23:36,583
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Louis, there's a clause
in the lease</b></i></font>

596
00:23:36,666 --> 00:23:38,835
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>that gives me
a 30-day out
and you know it.</b></i></font>

597
00:23:40,045 --> 00:23:41,088
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Stu, please.</b></i></font>

598
00:23:41,171 --> 00:23:42,756
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You cannot
do this to us now.</b></i></font>

599
00:23:43,381 --> 00:23:44,424
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Not tonight.</b></i></font>

600
00:23:44,508 --> 00:23:45,675
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm sorry, Louis.</b></i></font>

601
00:23:45,801 --> 00:23:46,927
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I hate to hang you
out to dry</b></i></font>

602
00:23:47,010 --> 00:23:48,762
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and if I could help you
in another way, I would.</b></i></font>

603
00:23:49,721 --> 00:23:51,515
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But we can't rent
this space.</b></i></font>

604
00:23:59,439 --> 00:24:00,941
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(GLASS SHATTERING)</b></i></font>

605
00:24:12,828 --> 00:24:13,954
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I have nothing
to say to you.</b></i></font>

606
00:24:15,163 --> 00:24:16,206
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Please, Mr. Forrest.</b></i></font>

607
00:24:16,289 --> 00:24:18,208
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You confronted me
when I didn't
want to talk to you</b></i></font>

608
00:24:18,291 --> 00:24:20,127
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and I gave you
the respect to hear
what you had to say.</b></i></font>

609
00:24:20,210 --> 00:24:22,129
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You can at least hear
what we have to say.</b></i></font>

610
00:24:22,295 --> 00:24:24,131
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You've got 60 seconds,
then I'm calling the police.</b></i></font>

611
00:24:24,214 --> 00:24:25,340
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>MIKE: Go ahead.
But when they get here,</b></i></font>

612
00:24:25,423 --> 00:24:27,384
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>we'll tell them
all about how you
sent Maria Gomez away</b></i></font>

613
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:28,552
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>so that
she couldn't testify.</b></i></font>

614
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:30,262
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>That's insane.
RACHEL: Is it?</b></i></font>

615
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:33,765
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Because a woman who was
never in the court record
as a drug user</b></i></font>

616
00:24:33,849 --> 00:24:36,143
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>went to a rehab facility
she could never afford.</b></i></font>

617
00:24:36,268 --> 00:24:37,936
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And you knew
enough about her
to call her a druggie</b></i></font>

618
00:24:38,019 --> 00:24:39,271
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>to my face a month ago.</b></i></font>

619
00:24:39,729 --> 00:24:40,772
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>That's not proof
of anything.</b></i></font>

620
00:24:40,856 --> 00:24:43,024
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>MIKE: And that's
not the answer of
an innocent man.</b></i></font>

621
00:24:43,358 --> 00:24:44,568
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Look, Mr. Forrest,</b></i></font>

622
00:24:45,777 --> 00:24:48,071
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I can't begin to understand
what you've been through.</b></i></font>

623
00:24:48,238 --> 00:24:49,656
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But right now,
the wrong man</b></i></font>

624
00:24:49,739 --> 00:24:51,908
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>is sitting on death row
because of what you did.</b></i></font>

625
00:24:52,409 --> 00:24:54,536
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I didn't do shit.
RACHEL: Please.</b></i></font>

626
00:24:54,744 --> 00:24:56,997
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Can you imagine
what this has been like
for Leonard Bailey?</b></i></font>

627
00:24:57,080 --> 00:25:00,083
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What his life
has looked like
for the past 12 years?</b></i></font>

628
00:25:00,542 --> 00:25:02,127
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>The only thing
I want to imagine</b></i></font>

629
00:25:02,210 --> 00:25:05,547
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>is what my life is going
to be like after that man
takes his final breath.</b></i></font>

630
00:25:05,797 --> 00:25:06,965
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Your time is up.</b></i></font>

631
00:25:11,553 --> 00:25:13,180
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(MACHINE WHIRRING)</b></i></font>

632
00:25:17,350 --> 00:25:18,768
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Louis, is everything okay?</b></i></font>

633
00:25:19,436 --> 00:25:20,770
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What do you mean?</b></i></font>

634
00:25:20,937 --> 00:25:22,772
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I mean, I saw
what happened with Stu.</b></i></font>

635
00:25:23,106 --> 00:25:24,858
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I know he's leaving,
but it's going to be okay.</b></i></font>

636
00:25:25,025 --> 00:25:26,359
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Harvey's gonna fix things
with Jim Reynolds.</b></i></font>

637
00:25:26,443 --> 00:25:27,694
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>We're gonna get
more clients.</b></i></font>

638
00:25:27,777 --> 00:25:29,029
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Tara's pregnant.</b></i></font>

639
00:25:30,864 --> 00:25:31,948
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>It's not mine.</b></i></font>

640
00:25:32,199 --> 00:25:33,200
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What did you tell her?</b></i></font>

641
00:25:33,283 --> 00:25:34,534
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I told her I'm going to
stay with her</b></i></font>

642
00:25:34,618 --> 00:25:35,952
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and support her
every way I can</b></i></font>

643
00:25:36,411 --> 00:25:37,454
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>because I'm in love
with her.</b></i></font>

644
00:25:37,537 --> 00:25:38,538
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And what did she say?</b></i></font>

645
00:25:38,622 --> 00:25:39,748
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>She said we need
to sleep on it</b></i></font>

646
00:25:39,831 --> 00:25:41,082
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>because it hasn't
sunk in for me.</b></i></font>

647
00:25:41,458 --> 00:25:42,751
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then what were
you so upset about?</b></i></font>

648
00:25:43,126 --> 00:25:45,503
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What if she's saying that
because she can't decide
what she's going to do?</b></i></font>

649
00:25:45,629 --> 00:25:47,172
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Louis.
How do I know
she didn't wake up</b></i></font>

650
00:25:47,255 --> 00:25:49,049
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>this morning and decide
to run back to him?</b></i></font>

651
00:25:49,132 --> 00:25:50,342
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>That's not
what's going on.</b></i></font>

652
00:25:50,550 --> 00:25:51,968
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>This is a huge decision,</b></i></font>

653
00:25:52,052 --> 00:25:54,512
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and she wants to
make sure that you're
in it for the long haul.</b></i></font>

654
00:25:54,596 --> 00:25:55,722
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Donna, I would never
go back on my word.</b></i></font>

655
00:25:55,805 --> 00:25:57,182
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>That's not true
and you know it.</b></i></font>

656
00:25:57,307 --> 00:25:58,516
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You make
impulsive decisions</b></i></font>

657
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:00,143
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and you go back on them
all the time.</b></i></font>

658
00:26:00,227 --> 00:26:01,311
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>This is different.
How?</b></i></font>

659
00:26:01,394 --> 00:26:02,437
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Because it's a baby!</b></i></font>

660
00:26:03,146 --> 00:26:04,731
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I would never do that
to a baby.</b></i></font>

661
00:26:04,981 --> 00:26:06,107
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I hear you.</b></i></font>

662
00:26:06,316 --> 00:26:08,985
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But all I'm saying is
don't do something rash.</b></i></font>

663
00:26:09,069 --> 00:26:11,321
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Because this isn't
something you can
change your mind about.</b></i></font>

664
00:26:15,575 --> 00:26:17,285
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You've got to
be kidding.</b></i></font>

665
00:26:17,369 --> 00:26:19,246
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You went to see
the victim's father
without telling me?</b></i></font>

666
00:26:19,788 --> 00:26:21,539
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Jessica, we didn't have time
and we had to know.</b></i></font>

667
00:26:21,623 --> 00:26:23,625
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And like you taught Harvey
and Harvey taught me,</b></i></font>

668
00:26:23,708 --> 00:26:25,168
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>it's better to
ask forgiveness
than permission.</b></i></font>

669
00:26:25,252 --> 00:26:26,836
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You're not asking
for either one.</b></i></font>

670
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:28,880
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You're asking me
to accuse the man</b></i></font>

671
00:26:28,964 --> 00:26:30,966
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>of obstruction of justice
in open court.</b></i></font>

672
00:26:31,049 --> 00:26:32,634
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Jessica, we looked
the man in the eye.</b></i></font>

673
00:26:32,717 --> 00:26:34,469
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And I'm telling you,
he did it.</b></i></font>

674
00:26:34,552 --> 00:26:36,429
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I don't give a shit
if he did it or not.</b></i></font>

675
00:26:36,513 --> 00:26:38,181
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>There's no way
on the planet
we can prove it.</b></i></font>

676
00:26:38,265 --> 00:26:40,308
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>We don't have to
prove it if you
break him on the stand.</b></i></font>

677
00:26:40,392 --> 00:26:42,018
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Are you out of
your goddamn mind?</b></i></font>

678
00:26:42,060 --> 00:26:44,062
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>It's the only way.
JESSICA:
It's not the only way!</b></i></font>

679
00:26:44,145 --> 00:26:45,230
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And I'm not doing it!</b></i></font>

680
00:26:45,355 --> 00:26:46,481
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What are you
so afraid of?</b></i></font>

681
00:26:46,648 --> 00:26:48,692
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Don't you dare
say that to me.</b></i></font>

682
00:26:49,859 --> 00:26:52,988
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>That man's life
is in my hands
because your fianc√©e</b></i></font>

683
00:26:53,238 --> 00:26:54,739
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>told him
not to take the deal.</b></i></font>

684
00:26:55,532 --> 00:26:57,701
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And if we attack the father
and it backfires,</b></i></font>

685
00:26:57,784 --> 00:27:00,370
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>we lose the jury for good
and his life is over!</b></i></font>

686
00:27:02,872 --> 00:27:07,085
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Jessica, this guy wants
to tell everyone the truth
because he's proud of it.</b></i></font>

687
00:27:07,836 --> 00:27:10,338
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You just need to lead him
right where he's dying to go.</b></i></font>

688
00:27:10,714 --> 00:27:12,048
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And what if
I can't do that?</b></i></font>

689
00:27:12,132 --> 00:27:13,341
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Mike has something
that might help.</b></i></font>

690
00:27:14,050 --> 00:27:15,218
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What are you
talking about?</b></i></font>

691
00:27:15,302 --> 00:27:17,846
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm asking
if you've seen the movie
A Few Good Men.</b></i></font>

692
00:27:23,310 --> 00:27:25,353
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Donna, what are
you doing here?
DONNA: Waiting for you.</b></i></font>

693
00:27:25,437 --> 00:27:26,896
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Because I've been
calling you
and texting you</b></i></font>

694
00:27:26,980 --> 00:27:28,189
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and you obviously
haven't checked
your phone.</b></i></font>

695
00:27:28,273 --> 00:27:29,566
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I haven't checked my phone
because I've been going</b></i></font>

696
00:27:29,649 --> 00:27:31,484
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>to every client we have
reassuring them</b></i></font>

697
00:27:31,568 --> 00:27:32,986
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>that Sutter's going to
recant his bullshit</b></i></font>

698
00:27:33,069 --> 00:27:34,279
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and Jim Reynolds
isn't going anywhere.</b></i></font>

699
00:27:34,362 --> 00:27:35,655
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Yeah, well,
if you don't
do something soon,</b></i></font>

700
00:27:35,739 --> 00:27:36,906
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>you're gonna
have to recant that.</b></i></font>

701
00:27:37,032 --> 00:27:38,783
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What the hell
are you talking about?
Jim Reynolds called.</b></i></font>

702
00:27:38,950 --> 00:27:40,368
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>They moved his board meeting
to tomorrow.</b></i></font>

703
00:27:51,796 --> 00:27:53,423
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>We need to talk.
JESSICA:
I don't believe this.</b></i></font>

704
00:27:53,506 --> 00:27:56,343
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm about to give the most
important cross-examination
in my life</b></i></font>

705
00:27:56,426 --> 00:27:57,761
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and you're showing up now?</b></i></font>

706
00:27:57,844 --> 00:27:59,262
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Jessica, we left you
a dozen messages.</b></i></font>

707
00:27:59,346 --> 00:28:01,181
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Jim Reynolds' board
moved up the meeting.</b></i></font>

708
00:28:01,264 --> 00:28:03,183
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then tell them
to push it back because
I can't go right now.</b></i></font>

709
00:28:03,266 --> 00:28:04,392
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>LOUIS: God damn it.
Don't you get it?</b></i></font>

710
00:28:04,476 --> 00:28:06,186
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>They moved it up
so they can get it
over with.</b></i></font>

711
00:28:06,269 --> 00:28:08,063
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>They're gonna fire Reynolds
and they're gonna fire us.</b></i></font>

712
00:28:08,146 --> 00:28:09,606
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And he made it clear
that you need to be there.</b></i></font>

713
00:28:09,689 --> 00:28:10,774
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>HARVEY: Jessica,
Louis is right.</b></i></font>

714
00:28:10,982 --> 00:28:12,025
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>If we show up
without you,</b></i></font>

715
00:28:12,108 --> 00:28:13,360
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>we might as well
not show up at all.</b></i></font>

716
00:28:14,235 --> 00:28:16,446
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>JUDGE EVANS:
Is the defense ready
to proceed?</b></i></font>

717
00:28:20,867 --> 00:28:23,411
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Your Honor, I'd like
to ask for a half-day
continuance.</b></i></font>

718
00:28:23,495 --> 00:28:24,537
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>On what grounds?</b></i></font>

719
00:28:24,621 --> 00:28:26,790
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>It has to do
with my law firm's survival.</b></i></font>

720
00:28:26,873 --> 00:28:28,541
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then let her associate
take the reins
for half a day.</b></i></font>

721
00:28:28,625 --> 00:28:29,751
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>She's not ready
for this.</b></i></font>

722
00:28:29,834 --> 00:28:30,877
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Well, she was ready
for the other thing.</b></i></font>

723
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:33,129
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>That was different
and the prosecution knows it.</b></i></font>

724
00:28:33,338 --> 00:28:35,382
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What I know is
whatever's happening
with your firm,</b></i></font>

725
00:28:35,465 --> 00:28:36,633
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>is not my concern.</b></i></font>

726
00:28:36,716 --> 00:28:38,468
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>So, either let your associate
handle this</b></i></font>

727
00:28:38,551 --> 00:28:42,097
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>or handle it yourself.
But this case
is moving forward.</b></i></font>

728
00:28:49,270 --> 00:28:50,814
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You do whatever you can.</b></i></font>

729
00:28:50,897 --> 00:28:54,192
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm not abandoning Leonard
to some corporate
power struggle.</b></i></font>

730
00:28:54,275 --> 00:28:56,069
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>This isn't a goddamn
power struggle.</b></i></font>

731
00:28:56,152 --> 00:28:57,654
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>We're going to go
out of business.</b></i></font>

732
00:28:57,862 --> 00:29:00,365
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I can't think about
that right now, Louis.</b></i></font>

733
00:29:00,448 --> 00:29:02,033
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>That man's life
is on the line</b></i></font>

734
00:29:02,117 --> 00:29:03,535
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and I'm not hanging him
out to dry.</b></i></font>

735
00:29:03,701 --> 00:29:05,245
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>JUDGE EVANS:
Miss Pearson,</b></i></font>

736
00:29:05,328 --> 00:29:06,913
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>are you ready
to proceed?</b></i></font>

737
00:29:08,248 --> 00:29:09,374
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>We are, Your Honor.</b></i></font>

738
00:29:10,333 --> 00:29:13,294
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Defense would like
to recall Victor Forrest
to the stand.</b></i></font>

739
00:29:24,139 --> 00:29:25,473
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>ALAN: Jessica,
what a surprise.</b></i></font>

740
00:29:25,557 --> 00:29:26,891
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You never come
to my office.</b></i></font>

741
00:29:29,018 --> 00:29:30,145
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>When did you get home
from school?</b></i></font>

742
00:29:30,228 --> 00:29:31,354
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>YOUNG JESSICA:
This morning.</b></i></font>

743
00:29:31,438 --> 00:29:32,480
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Well, if I'd known
you were coming, I...</b></i></font>

744
00:29:32,564 --> 00:29:33,940
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I didn't want you
to know, Dad.</b></i></font>

745
00:29:34,399 --> 00:29:35,859
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I have some news.
What is it?</b></i></font>

746
00:29:36,151 --> 00:29:37,193
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Is everything okay?</b></i></font>

747
00:29:37,277 --> 00:29:39,612
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I got into Harvard Law
next year. And I'm going.</b></i></font>

748
00:29:39,696 --> 00:29:41,322
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What?
I'm going to be a lawyer.</b></i></font>

749
00:29:41,990 --> 00:29:44,075
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What happened to our plan
of you becoming surgeon?</b></i></font>

750
00:29:44,159 --> 00:29:46,369
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>That was never
our plan, Dad.
It was always yours.</b></i></font>

751
00:29:46,453 --> 00:29:47,912
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Don't you speak
to me like that!</b></i></font>

752
00:29:47,996 --> 00:29:50,039
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm not speaking
to you like anything.</b></i></font>

753
00:29:50,498 --> 00:29:52,417
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm telling you the truth.
You want the truth?</b></i></font>

754
00:29:53,209 --> 00:29:54,294
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Doctors save lives</b></i></font>

755
00:29:54,377 --> 00:29:56,296
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and lawyers are nothing
but power-hungry
bottom-feeders.</b></i></font>

756
00:29:56,379 --> 00:29:58,381
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>They don't have to be
and I'm not going to be.</b></i></font>

757
00:29:58,465 --> 00:29:59,841
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And I raised you better.
No, Dad.</b></i></font>

758
00:29:59,924 --> 00:30:02,135
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You raised me
to do what inspires me.</b></i></font>

759
00:30:02,218 --> 00:30:04,095
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And what inspires me
is to be a lawyer.</b></i></font>

760
00:30:04,679 --> 00:30:06,014
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You go to that school,</b></i></font>

761
00:30:06,181 --> 00:30:08,016
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>you're going to get infected
with their lawyer mind-set.</b></i></font>

762
00:30:08,099 --> 00:30:09,559
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And when you come out,</b></i></font>

763
00:30:09,767 --> 00:30:11,811
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>you're not gonna
give a shit
about your fellow man.</b></i></font>

764
00:30:13,354 --> 00:30:16,274
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>If you think that,
then you should have
spent more time with me.</b></i></font>

765
00:30:18,067 --> 00:30:19,944
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Because you don't know me
at all.</b></i></font>

766
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:25,492
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(GAVEL POUNDS)</b></i></font>

767
00:30:28,745 --> 00:30:30,538
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>JUDGE EVANS: (ECHOING)
Miss Pearson.</b></i></font>

768
00:30:30,914 --> 00:30:32,415
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Ms. Pearson,
are you ready?</b></i></font>

769
00:30:44,052 --> 00:30:45,261
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Mr. Forrest?</b></i></font>

770
00:30:46,930 --> 00:30:48,890
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>So many lives
were ruined that night.</b></i></font>

771
00:30:51,059 --> 00:30:53,353
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Your daughter's,
her boyfriend's,</b></i></font>

772
00:30:53,895 --> 00:30:54,896
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>yours.</b></i></font>

773
00:30:55,104 --> 00:30:56,397
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Is there a question?</b></i></font>

774
00:30:56,523 --> 00:30:58,107
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Someone had to pay for that,
didn't they?</b></i></font>

775
00:30:58,191 --> 00:30:59,817
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Yeah, they sure
as hell did.</b></i></font>

776
00:30:59,901 --> 00:31:01,611
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Is that why you paid
for Maria Gomez
to go to rehab</b></i></font>

777
00:31:01,694 --> 00:31:04,447
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>to keep her from testifying
at Mr. Bailey's trial?</b></i></font>

778
00:31:04,781 --> 00:31:05,782
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What?</b></i></font>

779
00:31:05,865 --> 00:31:08,201
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Objection, Your Honor.
She's putting
the victim on trial.</b></i></font>

780
00:31:08,368 --> 00:31:10,203
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>My client is
the victim here.</b></i></font>

781
00:31:10,286 --> 00:31:11,913
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Ms. Pearson, you better
back this up fast.</b></i></font>

782
00:31:11,996 --> 00:31:13,456
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then ask the witness
to answer my question.</b></i></font>

783
00:31:13,623 --> 00:31:15,416
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I never even heard
of that woman
until yesterday.</b></i></font>

784
00:31:15,500 --> 00:31:17,877
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Your Honor,
the defense would like
to admit into evidence</b></i></font>

785
00:31:17,961 --> 00:31:20,505
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>the admissions form
for an Allison Dobsen</b></i></font>

786
00:31:20,588 --> 00:31:23,216
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>into the Pathways
Rehabilitation Center
from 12 years ago.</b></i></font>

787
00:31:23,299 --> 00:31:24,384
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What? Who is that?</b></i></font>

788
00:31:24,467 --> 00:31:25,718
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>She was
Maria Gomez's roommate</b></i></font>

789
00:31:25,802 --> 00:31:26,970
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and I'm going to
put her on the stand.</b></i></font>

790
00:31:27,053 --> 00:31:29,013
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>No, that can't be.
No, you can't do that.</b></i></font>

791
00:31:29,097 --> 00:31:31,015
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And she's going to say
that Maria told her</b></i></font>

792
00:31:31,099 --> 00:31:33,434
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>that she felt terrible
about abandoning her friend.</b></i></font>

793
00:31:33,518 --> 00:31:34,894
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Objection, hearsay.</b></i></font>

794
00:31:34,978 --> 00:31:36,062
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>No, she won't.
Overruled.</b></i></font>

795
00:31:36,145 --> 00:31:37,188
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>JESSICA:
And she's going to testify</b></i></font>

796
00:31:37,272 --> 00:31:38,898
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>that you paid
for Maria to be there.</b></i></font>

797
00:31:38,982 --> 00:31:40,108
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I had nothing to do
with anything!</b></i></font>

798
00:31:40,233 --> 00:31:42,235
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>That's not what
she's going to say.
I don't care. She's lying.</b></i></font>

799
00:31:42,318 --> 00:31:44,362
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Why would she lie?
She just wants to
put the record straight.</b></i></font>

800
00:31:44,487 --> 00:31:46,406
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>The record is straight.
Not according
to her roommate.</b></i></font>

801
00:31:46,489 --> 00:31:48,783
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>She's lying.
Objection, badgering.</b></i></font>

802
00:31:48,866 --> 00:31:50,243
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>How could you know?</b></i></font>

803
00:31:50,326 --> 00:31:52,245
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Because Maria Gomez
didn't have a roommate!</b></i></font>

804
00:31:53,871 --> 00:31:55,164
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>JESSICA:
What did you just say?</b></i></font>

805
00:31:55,248 --> 00:31:56,874
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>VICTOR:
Yes, I paid for her.</b></i></font>

806
00:31:56,958 --> 00:31:58,293
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>'Cause she's a junkie
who would say anything</b></i></font>

807
00:31:58,376 --> 00:31:59,419
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>to get him out
of what he did.</b></i></font>

808
00:31:59,502 --> 00:32:01,087
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>So, I got her out of the way
'cause he did it.</b></i></font>

809
00:32:01,170 --> 00:32:03,006
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Mr. Forrest.
He did it!</b></i></font>

810
00:32:13,391 --> 00:32:14,517
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Your Honor,</b></i></font>

811
00:32:15,518 --> 00:32:19,397
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>the defense asks
that Mr. Bailey
be exonerated</b></i></font>

812
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:21,899
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and his sentence
be commuted immediately.</b></i></font>

813
00:32:23,693 --> 00:32:24,861
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Mr. Marsden?</b></i></font>

814
00:32:26,738 --> 00:32:28,031
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>We have no objections,
Your Honor.</b></i></font>

815
00:32:28,239 --> 00:32:30,074
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then the jury
may be excused.</b></i></font>

816
00:32:30,199 --> 00:32:31,576
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And Mr. Bailey,</b></i></font>

817
00:32:32,452 --> 00:32:33,453
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>you're free.</b></i></font>

818
00:32:33,536 --> 00:32:34,537
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(GAVEL POUNDS)</b></i></font>

819
00:32:36,456 --> 00:32:37,957
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I can't believe it.</b></i></font>

820
00:32:38,041 --> 00:32:39,167
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>We did it.</b></i></font>

821
00:32:39,751 --> 00:32:40,752
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>RACHEL: We did it!</b></i></font>

822
00:32:40,835 --> 00:32:42,086
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(RACHEL LAUGHS)</b></i></font>

823
00:32:54,223 --> 00:32:56,851
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I can't
thank you enough.</b></i></font>

824
00:32:57,602 --> 00:32:59,562
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You don't have to
thank me, Leonard.</b></i></font>

825
00:33:01,564 --> 00:33:03,524
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You just have to
walk out that door.</b></i></font>

826
00:33:17,497 --> 00:33:18,498
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(SIGHS)</b></i></font>

827
00:33:36,557 --> 00:33:38,142
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>That was
one hell of a cross.</b></i></font>

828
00:33:38,226 --> 00:33:40,395
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>JESSICA:
Well, I'd like to say
it was no big deal,</b></i></font>

829
00:33:40,478 --> 00:33:42,021
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>but I'd be lying
if I didn't say it was</b></i></font>

830
00:33:42,105 --> 00:33:44,315
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>the most satisfying moment
of my entire career.</b></i></font>

831
00:33:45,817 --> 00:33:46,943
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What's this?</b></i></font>

832
00:33:47,276 --> 00:33:48,945
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I got a call
from Jim Reynolds.</b></i></font>

833
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:50,863
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>He said that
if you didn't show today,</b></i></font>

834
00:33:50,947 --> 00:33:52,115
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>they were gonna sign with me.</b></i></font>

835
00:33:52,448 --> 00:33:54,033
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And we both know
you didn't show.</b></i></font>

836
00:33:54,826 --> 00:33:55,993
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You want to merge?</b></i></font>

837
00:33:58,621 --> 00:34:00,540
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I said all that stuff
about rivals</b></i></font>

838
00:34:00,623 --> 00:34:03,042
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>because I didn't
want to say this
in front of Harvey.</b></i></font>

839
00:34:03,793 --> 00:34:06,003
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But I know you tanked
the Sutter case for Mike.</b></i></font>

840
00:34:06,754 --> 00:34:08,840
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And I can see
what you've been
doing for Rachel.</b></i></font>

841
00:34:09,132 --> 00:34:11,217
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>So, this isn't
just professional.</b></i></font>

842
00:34:12,176 --> 00:34:13,386
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>For me,
it's personal.</b></i></font>

843
00:34:13,803 --> 00:34:16,389
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Robert...
Jessica, you got
knocked down the mountain.</b></i></font>

844
00:34:16,472 --> 00:34:18,933
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And without help,
you're not going to
be able to get back up.</b></i></font>

845
00:34:20,309 --> 00:34:22,603
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Please, take my hand.</b></i></font>

846
00:34:22,687 --> 00:34:24,147
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I appreciate your offer</b></i></font>

847
00:34:25,064 --> 00:34:26,983
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>more than you know, Robert.</b></i></font>

848
00:34:28,192 --> 00:34:30,737
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But I've had my name
first for too long.</b></i></font>

849
00:34:30,820 --> 00:34:32,613
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I can't go back
to having it last.</b></i></font>

850
00:34:32,864 --> 00:34:34,198
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Jessica,
if you don't do this,</b></i></font>

851
00:34:34,282 --> 00:34:35,575
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>you're not gonna
have it anywhere.</b></i></font>

852
00:34:35,658 --> 00:34:36,784
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then so be it.</b></i></font>

853
00:34:37,493 --> 00:34:40,371
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Besides, we both know
lawyers are nothing</b></i></font>

854
00:34:40,455 --> 00:34:43,291
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>but power-hungry
bottom-feeders, anyway.</b></i></font>

855
00:34:57,180 --> 00:34:58,973
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>MANNIS: You two don't look
like Jessica Pearson.</b></i></font>

856
00:34:59,056 --> 00:35:01,100
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then again,
it doesn't really matter,</b></i></font>

857
00:35:01,184 --> 00:35:02,268
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>because in 15 minutes,</b></i></font>

858
00:35:02,351 --> 00:35:04,479
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>your firm is no longer
going to be</b></i></font>

859
00:35:04,604 --> 00:35:06,814
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>in the employ
of this company.
HARVEY: Maybe not.</b></i></font>

860
00:35:07,356 --> 00:35:08,816
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But while we are,</b></i></font>

861
00:35:08,900 --> 00:35:10,568
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I think you're gonna need
one more chair.</b></i></font>

862
00:35:10,693 --> 00:35:11,903
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What are you
talking about?</b></i></font>

863
00:35:12,236 --> 00:35:13,863
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>We're talking
about your brand new
largest shareholder.</b></i></font>

864
00:35:13,946 --> 00:35:16,908
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What shareholder?
Hey, guy.
Stu Buzzini.</b></i></font>

865
00:35:17,241 --> 00:35:18,951
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>This one
at the head of the table
looks good to me.</b></i></font>

866
00:35:19,035 --> 00:35:20,036
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(CLEARS THROAT)</b></i></font>

867
00:35:20,119 --> 00:35:22,246
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I don't care who you are
or how many shares
you bought,</b></i></font>

868
00:35:22,330 --> 00:35:23,748
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>you're not a member
of this board.</b></i></font>

869
00:35:23,915 --> 00:35:25,583
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>STU: No.
But as of next quarter,
I will be.</b></i></font>

870
00:35:25,666 --> 00:35:27,502
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>So, either you keep
these two as your lawyers</b></i></font>

871
00:35:27,585 --> 00:35:29,295
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and Jim Reynolds
as your CEO</b></i></font>

872
00:35:29,378 --> 00:35:31,839
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>or at our next meeting,
you'll be out on your ass.</b></i></font>

873
00:35:31,923 --> 00:35:34,175
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You can't do this to me.
That's where
you're wrong, Donald.</b></i></font>

874
00:35:34,258 --> 00:35:35,802
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>We can and we did.</b></i></font>

875
00:35:35,885 --> 00:35:37,553
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Because he just bought up
your company</b></i></font>

876
00:35:37,637 --> 00:35:39,722
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and you messed with
the wrong goddamn Marine.</b></i></font>

877
00:35:39,806 --> 00:35:41,140
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What the hell
are you talking about?</b></i></font>

878
00:35:41,224 --> 00:35:42,225
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Yeah, what are you
talking about?</b></i></font>

879
00:35:42,308 --> 00:35:43,476
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>He's quoting
A Few Good Men.</b></i></font>

880
00:35:43,559 --> 00:35:45,061
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Finally,
somebody gets me!</b></i></font>

881
00:35:45,144 --> 00:35:46,938
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I got your back, bro.
Don't "bro" me, dude.</b></i></font>

882
00:35:47,021 --> 00:35:48,064
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You got it, Chief.</b></i></font>

883
00:35:48,189 --> 00:35:50,316
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Hey, can I
get in on this?
HARVEY AND STU: No.</b></i></font>

884
00:35:52,902 --> 00:35:55,613
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)</b></i></font>

885
00:35:55,696 --> 00:35:56,823
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(KEYS JANGLING)</b></i></font>

886
00:35:59,826 --> 00:36:00,910
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>RACHEL: Hey.</b></i></font>

887
00:36:02,245 --> 00:36:03,538
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I got you a present.</b></i></font>

888
00:36:03,621 --> 00:36:04,622
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(CHUCKLES)</b></i></font>

889
00:36:07,166 --> 00:36:09,836
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You didn't
have to do that.</b></i></font>

890
00:36:09,919 --> 00:36:11,045
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I know.</b></i></font>

891
00:36:13,798 --> 00:36:15,383
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I know we're not supposed
to take pictures in there,</b></i></font>

892
00:36:15,466 --> 00:36:17,009
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>but I couldn't
help myself.</b></i></font>

893
00:36:20,763 --> 00:36:22,473
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>This is unbelievable.</b></i></font>

894
00:36:22,557 --> 00:36:23,599
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>No.</b></i></font>

895
00:36:24,141 --> 00:36:27,019
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What you did for that man
is unbelievable.</b></i></font>

896
00:36:37,113 --> 00:36:38,739
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Harvey offered me a job.</b></i></font>

897
00:36:40,575 --> 00:36:44,453
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Go back to the firm
as a consultant.</b></i></font>

898
00:36:46,455 --> 00:36:47,790
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What are you gonna do?</b></i></font>

899
00:36:49,333 --> 00:36:50,418
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I don't know.</b></i></font>

900
00:37:02,138 --> 00:37:04,307
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>HARVEY: What is that,
a cup of tea?</b></i></font>

901
00:37:04,390 --> 00:37:06,350
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Just a moment
of quiet reflection.</b></i></font>

902
00:37:06,642 --> 00:37:07,643
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Well, to hell with that.</b></i></font>

903
00:37:07,727 --> 00:37:09,270
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>This is a moment
for celebration.</b></i></font>

904
00:37:09,353 --> 00:37:10,354
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>That's right.</b></i></font>

905
00:37:10,813 --> 00:37:13,274
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Because a man's life
wasn't the only thing
saved today.</b></i></font>

906
00:37:13,482 --> 00:37:14,650
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Don't tell me.</b></i></font>

907
00:37:14,734 --> 00:37:17,028
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You managed to lock down
Jim Reynolds after all.</b></i></font>

908
00:37:17,111 --> 00:37:18,863
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>We did.</b></i></font>

909
00:37:18,946 --> 00:37:20,698
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>The firm is safe,
Jessica.</b></i></font>

910
00:37:21,782 --> 00:37:22,909
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Thank you.</b></i></font>

911
00:37:28,998 --> 00:37:30,750
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But it's not
my firm anymore.</b></i></font>

912
00:37:34,712 --> 00:37:35,796
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>It's yours.</b></i></font>

913
00:37:36,213 --> 00:37:37,465
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What do you mean, ours?</b></i></font>

914
00:37:37,590 --> 00:37:39,634
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I mean, I've decided
to step down.</b></i></font>

915
00:37:39,800 --> 00:37:40,843
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What?
Jessica.</b></i></font>

916
00:37:40,927 --> 00:37:42,511
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Listen.
Somewhere along the way,</b></i></font>

917
00:37:42,595 --> 00:37:45,222
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I forgot why I became
a lawyer in the first place.</b></i></font>

918
00:37:45,306 --> 00:37:47,934
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And it wasn't just to fight
for money and power.</b></i></font>

919
00:37:48,017 --> 00:37:50,102
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>It was to fight
for something more.
LOUIS: Bullshit.</b></i></font>

920
00:37:50,186 --> 00:37:51,896
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You're not fighting
for something more,
you're running away.</b></i></font>

921
00:37:51,979 --> 00:37:53,064
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Louis.
No. We bust our ass</b></i></font>

922
00:37:53,147 --> 00:37:54,523
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>to save this goddamn place?</b></i></font>

923
00:37:54,649 --> 00:37:56,609
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>She decides
to up and leave?
We committed to this.</b></i></font>

924
00:37:56,692 --> 00:37:58,569
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>HARVEY: Louis, she isn't
doing this to you!</b></i></font>

925
00:37:58,653 --> 00:37:59,946
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>She's doing it
for herself.</b></i></font>

926
00:38:00,029 --> 00:38:01,614
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I don't give a shit
why she's doing it.</b></i></font>

927
00:38:01,697 --> 00:38:03,449
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>It's selfish
and self-serving</b></i></font>

928
00:38:03,532 --> 00:38:05,076
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and it's not gonna happen.</b></i></font>

929
00:38:05,159 --> 00:38:07,411
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Do you think I want
to goddamn do this, Louis?</b></i></font>

930
00:38:08,037 --> 00:38:09,246
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I have to do this.</b></i></font>

931
00:38:09,372 --> 00:38:10,790
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You can't just
throw this all away</b></i></font>

932
00:38:10,873 --> 00:38:12,750
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>after we gave
everything to save it.</b></i></font>

933
00:38:12,833 --> 00:38:14,251
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>DONNA:
That's enough.</b></i></font>

934
00:38:14,794 --> 00:38:16,045
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Louis,
after the partners left,</b></i></font>

935
00:38:16,128 --> 00:38:17,505
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>we swore we were
gonna dedicate</b></i></font>

936
00:38:17,588 --> 00:38:20,758
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>every ounce of blood,
sweat, and tears we had
to this place.</b></i></font>

937
00:38:21,759 --> 00:38:23,052
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But we didn't.</b></i></font>

938
00:38:24,053 --> 00:38:26,305
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Harvey and I focused
on getting Mike out.</b></i></font>

939
00:38:26,389 --> 00:38:28,474
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Jessica and Rachel
focused on
Leonard Bailey.</b></i></font>

940
00:38:28,557 --> 00:38:31,143
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And you focused
on finding love
in your life.</b></i></font>

941
00:38:33,813 --> 00:38:35,231
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>That's not true.</b></i></font>

942
00:38:35,314 --> 00:38:36,691
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Yes, it is.</b></i></font>

943
00:38:41,070 --> 00:38:42,947
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm not ready
to give up the firm.</b></i></font>

944
00:38:43,030 --> 00:38:45,408
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>JESSICA: No one's
saying you have to
give up the firm, Louis.</b></i></font>

945
00:38:48,077 --> 00:38:50,246
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(VOICE BREAKS)
You just have
to let me go.</b></i></font>

946
00:38:53,374 --> 00:38:54,917
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You sure about this?</b></i></font>

947
00:38:57,086 --> 00:38:58,587
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>To tell you the truth,</b></i></font>

948
00:38:59,505 --> 00:39:01,716
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>for the first time
in my life,</b></i></font>

949
00:39:01,799 --> 00:39:03,300
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm not sure
about anything.</b></i></font>

950
00:39:03,384 --> 00:39:05,428
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And it scares
the shit out of me.</b></i></font>

951
00:39:06,929 --> 00:39:08,764
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But I'm sure
I have to do this.</b></i></font>

952
00:39:13,769 --> 00:39:15,771
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>To Pearson Specter Litt.</b></i></font>

953
00:39:22,236 --> 00:39:24,488
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>JESSICA AND LOUIS:
To Pearson Specter Litt.</b></i></font>

954
00:39:59,190 --> 00:40:00,274
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>(KNOCKING)</b></i></font>

955
00:40:00,357 --> 00:40:01,400
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You busy?</b></i></font>

956
00:40:02,068 --> 00:40:03,152
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Of course not.</b></i></font>

957
00:40:03,402 --> 00:40:04,779
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I know you told me
to sleep on it.</b></i></font>

958
00:40:05,321 --> 00:40:08,365
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I didn't know
if that meant take
a day, two days.</b></i></font>

959
00:40:09,408 --> 00:40:10,910
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I've never really been
in this position before.</b></i></font>

960
00:40:10,993 --> 00:40:12,912
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Louis, I'm sorry...
Here's the thing.</b></i></font>

961
00:40:14,497 --> 00:40:16,582
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I tried to sleep on it,</b></i></font>

962
00:40:16,665 --> 00:40:19,460
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and all I could do
was picture a life
without you</b></i></font>

963
00:40:19,543 --> 00:40:21,253
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and your beautiful
unborn baby.</b></i></font>

964
00:40:21,378 --> 00:40:24,799
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And it just made me crazy
to think I wouldn't
be a part of it.</b></i></font>

965
00:40:26,050 --> 00:40:27,426
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But, Tara,
you need to know</b></i></font>

966
00:40:27,510 --> 00:40:29,303
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>that I am not
gonna say yes today</b></i></font>

967
00:40:29,386 --> 00:40:31,388
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>and change my mind tomorrow.</b></i></font>

968
00:40:32,181 --> 00:40:34,100
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>And I don't know
how to give you
that reassurance</b></i></font>

969
00:40:34,183 --> 00:40:36,185
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>without asking you
something first.</b></i></font>

970
00:40:41,774 --> 00:40:43,025
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Oh, my God, Louis.</b></i></font>

971
00:40:46,028 --> 00:40:47,738
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Tara Messer.</b></i></font>

972
00:40:48,864 --> 00:40:50,199
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Will you marry me?</b></i></font>

973
00:40:53,202 --> 00:40:55,788
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Yes, Louis,
I'll marry you.
(CHUCKLES)</b></i></font>

974
00:41:03,045 --> 00:41:04,171
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Oh.</b></i></font>

975
00:41:18,269 --> 00:41:19,395
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>JEFF: Jessica.</b></i></font>

976
00:41:20,729 --> 00:41:21,981
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What are you doing here?</b></i></font>

977
00:41:22,064 --> 00:41:25,317
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I wanted to talk to you
before you left
for Chicago.</b></i></font>

978
00:41:25,401 --> 00:41:26,527
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm glad.</b></i></font>

979
00:41:26,610 --> 00:41:28,362
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But I wouldn't have left
without saying goodbye.</b></i></font>

980
00:41:28,612 --> 00:41:30,739
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I didn't just come here
to say goodbye.</b></i></font>

981
00:41:34,243 --> 00:41:37,371
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I came to see
what you think about
me coming with you.</b></i></font>

982
00:41:38,664 --> 00:41:39,915
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>What about the firm?</b></i></font>

983
00:41:40,082 --> 00:41:41,542
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm leaving the firm.</b></i></font>

984
00:41:42,418 --> 00:41:44,920
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Jessica, if you're
walking away from
everything for me...</b></i></font>

985
00:41:45,004 --> 00:41:46,589
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>No, I'm not doing this
just for you.</b></i></font>

986
00:41:48,090 --> 00:41:49,592
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I'm doing this for me.</b></i></font>

987
00:41:52,887 --> 00:41:55,222
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>I don't want to be
a corporate lawyer anymore.</b></i></font>

988
00:41:56,640 --> 00:42:02,104
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>So, if you don't want me
to come to Chicago with you,
I won't.</b></i></font>

989
00:42:04,481 --> 00:42:07,943
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But I'm walking away,
no matter what.</b></i></font>

990
00:42:14,658 --> 00:42:15,993
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>Then walk away with me.</b></i></font>

991
00:42:41,060 --> 00:42:42,645
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You going to be okay?</b></i></font>

992
00:42:43,812 --> 00:42:45,356
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>HARVEY:
She was my mentor.</b></i></font>

993
00:42:48,067 --> 00:42:49,818
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>But, yeah,
I'm gonna be okay.</b></i></font>

994
00:42:53,155 --> 00:42:54,490
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>You want to be alone?</b></i></font>

995
00:42:56,533 --> 00:42:57,618
<font color=#FFFF00><i><b>No.</b></i></font>

